# ============================================================================
# 19. CURSOR COMPOSER USAGE TIPS
# ============================================================================

When using Cursor Composer for this project, follow these patterns:

FOR BACKEND TASKS (multi-file modules):
  1. Open Composer (Cmd+I)
  2. @-reference the relevant schema file: @packages/db/schema.ts
  3. @-reference related service files if they exist
  4. Paste the relevant prompt from the MVP Plan document
  5. Ask for ALL files in the module in one session
  6. Review the diff carefully — check RBAC, org isolation, error handling

FOR FRONTEND TASKS (screens and components):
  1. @-reference the component library: @packages/ui/src/index.ts
  2. @-reference the API types: @packages/types/src/index.ts
  3. @-reference TanStack Query hooks if they exist: @apps/web/lib/api.ts
  4. Generate the screen — Cursor Tab will autocomplete Tailwind classes
  5. Run axe-core check before committing

FOR DEBUGGING:
  1. Select the problematic code block
  2. Cmd+K → "Why is this failing the WCAG 1.4.3 contrast check?"
  3. Or: "Fix the keyboard trap in this modal component"

CONTEXT MANAGEMENT (compensates for Cursor's ~120k token limit):
  - When working on scanner: always @packages/db/schema.ts + @apps/api/src/scanner/types.ts
  - When working on portal: always @packages/ui/src + @packages/types/src
  - When working on billing: always @apps/api/src/billing + @packages/db/schema.ts
  - Start each major module in a fresh Composer session

# ============================================================================
# 20. QUICK REFERENCE — MOST COMMON PATTERNS
# ============================================================================

PROTECTED API ROUTE TEMPLATE:
  router.get('/assets', authenticate, requireRole(['customer_admin', 'accessibility_officer']),
    async (req: AuthRequest, res: Response) => {
      const { orgId } = req.user
      const assets = await db.select().from(assetsTable)
        .where(and(eq(assetsTable.organisationId, orgId), isNull(assetsTable.deletedAt)))
      res.json({ data: assets })
    })

ACCESSIBLE FORM FIELD TEMPLATE:
  <div className="space-y-1.5">
    <label htmlFor={id} className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
      {label}{required && <span aria-label="required" className="text-red-600 ml-0.5">*</span>}
    </label>
    <input
      id={id} name={name} type={type}
      aria-required={required} aria-invalid={!!error}
      aria-describedby={error ? `${id}-error` : hint ? `${id}-hint` : undefined}
      className={cn("w-full rounded-md border px-3 py-2 text-base focus-visible:outline-none
        focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary-600 focus-visible:ring-offset-2",
        error ? "border-red-500" : "border-gray-300")}
    />
    {hint && <p id={`${id}-hint`} className="text-sm text-gray-500">{hint}</p>}
    {error && <p id={`${id}-error`} role="alert" className="text-sm text-red-700">{error}</p>}
  </div>

MODAL WITH FOCUS TRAP TEMPLATE:
  <Dialog.Root open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
    <Dialog.Portal>
      <Dialog.Overlay className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50" />
      <Dialog.Content
        className="fixed top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 ..."
        aria-labelledby="dialog-title"
        aria-describedby="dialog-description">
        <Dialog.Title id="dialog-title">{title}</Dialog.Title>
        <Dialog.Description id="dialog-description" className="sr-only">{description}</Dialog.Description>
        {children}
        <Dialog.Close asChild>
          <button aria-label="Close dialog" className="...">×</button>
        </Dialog.Close>
      </Dialog.Content>
    </Dialog.Portal>
  </Dialog.Root>

SEVERITY BADGE TEMPLATE (never colour alone):
  const severityConfig = {
    critical: { label: 'Critical', icon: 'AlertCircle', bg: 'bg-red-100', text: 'text-red-800', border: 'border-red-200' },
    serious:  { label: 'Serious',  icon: 'AlertTriangle', bg: 'bg-amber-100', text: 'text-amber-800', border: 'border-amber-200' },
    moderate: { label: 'Moderate', icon: 'Info', bg: 'bg-blue-100', text: 'text-blue-800', border: 'border-blue-200' },
    minor:    { label: 'Minor',    icon: 'Minus', bg: 'bg-gray-100', text: 'text-gray-700', border: 'border-gray-200' },
  }
  // Usage: always renders icon + text + colour (WCAG 1.4.1 — not colour alone)
  <span className={cn('inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium border',
    severityConfig[severity].bg, severityConfig[severity].text, severityConfig[severity].border)}>
    <Icon name={severityConfig[severity].icon} size={12} aria-hidden="true" />
    {severityConfig[severity].label}
  </span>

INR AMOUNT FORMATTER:
  const formatINR = (paise: number): string =>
    new Intl.NumberFormat('en-IN', { style: 'currency', currency: 'INR',
      maximumFractionDigits: 0 }).format(paise / 100)
  // formatINR(399900) → "₹3,999"
  // formatINR(12345678) → "₹1,23,457"

PREFERS-REDUCED-MOTION CHECK:
  // In React
  const prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches
  // In Framer Motion
  <motion.div animate={prefersReducedMotion ? {} : { opacity: 1, y: 0 }} />
  // In CSS (always include)
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { * { animation-duration: 0.01ms !important; } }

